.TH "pvrdma_alloc_mr" 9 "pvrdma_alloc_mr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pvrdma_alloc_mr \- allocate a memory region
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ib_mr *" pvrdma_alloc_mr
.BI "(struct ib_pd *pd "  ","
.BI "enum ib_mr_type mr_type "  ","
.BI "u32 max_num_sg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pd" 12
protection domain
.IP "mr_type" 12
type of memory region
.IP "max_num_sg" 12
maximum number of pages
.SH "RETURN"
ib_mr pointer on success, otherwise returns an errno.
